User Instructions:

	To register your institution as a Member:

		1. Navigate to the "Register" tab on the top
		2. Write your Institution Name
		3. Click "REGISTER" (This will invoke consuming gas)
		4. If you confirm, the registration is complete

	To Submit a Genome into the Application:

		1. Navigate to the Home page using the "Athenomics" tab on the top (If you're not in the home tab)
		2. Click "Choose File"
		3. Navigate to your FASTA(.fa) file including your Genome
		4. Click "Open"
		5. Enter your soure in the "Source" Section on the right
		6. Click Submit (This will invoke consuming gas)
		7. If you confirm, the submission is complete
		8. Refresh the page to confirm your genome

	To Create a Request for a Genome:

		1. Navigate to the Home page using the "Athenomics" tab on the top (If you're not in the home tab)
		2. All publicly available genomes will be present in the "Publically Available Genomes" table.
		3. Click the button on the right of the genome that you need to create a request. (This will invoke consuming gas) <- {SOO: WILL THIS CONSUME GAS?}
		(IMPORTANT NOTE: You cannot make a request to a Genome that you own.)
		4. If you confirm, the request will be made.
		5. Navigate to the "Pending Requests" tab to confirm that your request has been made.

	To View Requests that others have made with your Genome:
		1. Navigate to the "Open Requests" tab on the top.
		2. Review the request information 
		3. If you wish to update the request status(Reject/Accept), click "Accept" to accept OR "Reject" to reject. (This will invoke consuming gas) <- {SOO: WILL THIS CONSUME GAS?}
		4. If you confirm, the request status will be updated.
		5. Refresh the page to confirm that the request has been successfully updated


	To View Requests that you have made to others' Genomes:
		1. Navigate to the "Pending Requests" tab on the top.
		2. If the request is still pending, it will display "Pending".
		3. If the request has been rejected, it will _________           <- {SOO: I dont know what this does}
		4. If the request has been accepted, the Button in the "Status" tab will be activated, allowing you to access the genome file.